5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to crimes and offenses; to amend Section
10 13A-6-142, Code of Alabama 1975, to further provide for the
11 jurisdiction over prosecutions for violations of domestic
12 violence protection orders.
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
14 Section 1. Section 13A-6-142, Code of Alabama 1975, is
15 amended to read as follows:
16 "§13A-6-142
17 (a) A person commits the crime of violation of a
18 domestic violence protection order if the person knowingly
19 commits any act prohibited by a domestic violence protection
20 order or willfully fails to abide by any term of a domestic
21 violence protection order.
22 (b) A violation of a domestic violence protection order
23 is a Class A misdemeanor which shall be punishable as provided
24 by law. A second conviction for violation of a domestic
25 violence protection order, in addition to any other penalty or
26 fine, shall be punishable by a minimum of 30 days imprisonment
27 which may not be suspended. A third or subsequent conviction
28 is a Class C felony.
Page 1

is a Class C felony.
SB173 Engrossed
29 (c) In addition to any other fine or penalty provided
30 by law, the court shall order the defendant to pay an
31 additional fine of fifty dollars ($50) for a violation of a
32 domestic violence protection order to be distributed to the
33 Domestic Violence Trust Fund, established by Section 30-6-11.
34 (d) Except for violations of this section that are
35 under the jurisdiction of the juvenile courts of this state,
36 the district courts of this state shall have exclusive
37 original jurisdiction over prosecutions for violations of this
38 section or any other prosecution for an action that would
39 constitute a violation of this section except as provided in
40 Section 12-12-32.
41 (e) Except for violations of this section that are
42 under the jurisdiction of the juvenile courts of this state,
43 any prosecution for a violation of this section, or any other
44 prosecution for an action that would constitute a violation of
45 this section, that is pending on October 1, 2026, shall be
46 transferred to the district court."
47 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
48 1, 2026.
